Convert an e00 file to a binary coverage

Source: R/e00-convert.R
e00_convert.Rd

Convert an e00 file to a binary coverage

e00_convert(e00, coverage = e00_temp_coverage(), coverage_type = c("V7", "PC"))

Arguments

e00

Path to a .e00 file.
coverage

An directory name whose name is less than 13 characters. long.
coverage_type

One of "V7" or "PC".

Value

The value of coverage.

Examples

e00 <- system.file("e00/cis_20170911.e00", package = "arce00")
coverage <- e00_convert(e00)
sf::st_read(coverage, layer = "LAB")

#> Reading layer `LAB' from data source `/private/var/folders/24/8k48jl6d249_n_qfxwsl6xvm0000gn/T/Rtmp22E0DC/file61e730034e4/SwlKLUUEdLiee' using driver `AVCBin'
#> Simple feature collection with 87 features and 68 fields

unlink(coverage, recursive = TRUE)
